sense.name: authority
sense.commentary: authorization, authorisation, say-so - the power or right to give orders or make decisions
sense.examples: He has the dominance to issue warrants. He lets his dominance over the employees get to his head.

sense.name: control
sense.commentary: DOMINANCE[+event] ascendance, ascendence, ascendancy, ascendency, control - the state that exists when one person or group has power over another
sense.examples: Her apparent dominance of her husband was really her attempt to make him pay attention to her.

sense.name: laterality
sense.commentary: superior development of one side of the body
sense.examples: Dominance is especially prevalent in the Gorn family.
